comments.body:
Updating to Foundation 5.5.1 breaks the Sass machinery, spewing out an endless loop of the following errors in a terminal session when running 'compass watch'...

{code}
error eucaconsole/static/sass/pages/login.scss (Line 13 of eucaconsole/static/sass/foundation/_functions.scss: Invalid CSS after "...ules: $modules ": expected "}", was "!global;")
{code}

With the site completely broken due to the Sass compilation errors.  Working on tracking the problem and determining if there's a workaround.

That's the bad news.  The good news is using Bower to install Foundation 5.0.3 appears to have resolved GUI-1127 -- need to confirm with more manual testing.

[~alice]: Look in the eucaconsole/static/js/thirdparty/foundation folder and open one of the modules (e.g. foundation.abide.js) and look for a line with the following...

{code}
version : '5.5.1'
{code}

...indicating we're at Foundation 5.5.1
